00:00:28.990 --> 00:00:32.049
We have a very exciting session
today about one of the

00:00:32.049 --> 00:00:33.980
coolest products at Google.

00:00:33.980 --> 00:00:37.530
And our special guest is Robin
Dua, head of product

00:00:37.530 --> 00:00:39.250
management for Google Wallet.

00:00:39.250 --> 00:00:42.410
And of course, we're going
to talk about all the new

00:00:42.410 --> 00:00:44.720
exciting developments around
Google Wallet.

00:00:44.720 --> 00:00:46.430
So let's start with an
easy question, Robin.

00:00:46.430 --> 00:00:48.110
What is Google Wallet?

00:00:48.110 --> 00:00:48.410
ROBIN DUA: Great.

00:00:48.410 --> 00:00:50.740
Well, first off, thanks for
having me here today.

00:00:50.740 --> 00:00:54.040
Google Wallet is an electronic
wallet that allows you to

00:00:54.040 --> 00:00:57.250
store all your credit cards,
debit cards, loyalty programs,

00:00:57.250 --> 00:01:00.580
as well as offers that you've
clipped from different places,

00:01:00.580 --> 00:01:03.800
all in one place that are easily
accessible through your

00:01:03.800 --> 00:01:05.519
phone as well as online.

00:01:05.519 --> 00:01:09.330
Users could access their Wallet
both online as well as

00:01:09.330 --> 00:01:11.540
through their phone for
making purchases.

00:01:11.540 --> 00:01:14.720
And it's also a great way for
users to be able to discover

00:01:14.720 --> 00:01:19.554
great offers that they're
interested in and save money.

00:01:19.554 --> 00:01:20.000
MIHAI IONESCU: Great.

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:22.610
So we recently announced
that we moved all

00:01:22.610 --> 00:01:23.690
cards to the cloud.

00:01:23.690 --> 00:01:25.815
Can you tell us a little bit
more about the technology

00:01:25.815 --> 00:01:27.400
behind this transition?

00:01:27.400 --> 00:01:27.820
ROBIN DUA: Sure.

00:01:27.820 --> 00:01:32.200
Well, let me just start by
talking a little bit about the

00:01:32.200 --> 00:01:34.860
momentum that has really
accelerated around the product

00:01:34.860 --> 00:01:36.520
since we launched Google
Wallet back in

00:01:36.520 --> 00:01:38.120
September of last year.

00:01:38.120 --> 00:01:41.920
We started with one bank
partner, which was Citibank,

00:01:41.920 --> 00:01:45.640
and we had one carrier
partner, Sprint.

00:01:45.640 --> 00:01:49.390
And users were only able to use
a single device when we

00:01:49.390 --> 00:01:52.260
launched, which was the
Nexus S device.

00:01:52.260 --> 00:01:56.980
And since then, we now support
a total of six devices on two

00:01:56.980 --> 00:02:00.550
carrier networks, both Virgin
Mobile as well as Sprint.

00:02:00.550 --> 00:02:04.920
And there's 25 national
retailers that are showcasing

00:02:04.920 --> 00:02:07.950
the full Google Wallet user
experience that combines

00:02:07.950 --> 00:02:11.830
offers, payments, loyalty as
part of our single-tap user

00:02:11.830 --> 00:02:13.530
experience that we created.

00:02:13.530 --> 00:02:16.970
And what single-tap allows a
user to do is with one tap

00:02:16.970 --> 00:02:20.370
they're able to transmit their
payment information, their

00:02:20.370 --> 00:02:24.150
loyalty information, as well as
coupons that they're trying

00:02:24.150 --> 00:02:27.830
to redeem, all with
a single action.

00:02:27.830 --> 00:02:33.080
And these national retailers
have done a special

00:02:33.080 --> 00:02:35.490
integration to create that
user experience in their

00:02:35.490 --> 00:02:39.960
stores as part of the purchasing
experience.

00:02:39.960 --> 00:02:44.450
We also have a total of about
200,000 locations where users

00:02:44.450 --> 00:02:46.950
could actually tap their phone
and pay for things using

00:02:46.950 --> 00:02:48.710
Google Wallet.

00:02:48.710 --> 00:02:51.780
And that number is continuing to
increase month over month.

00:02:51.780 --> 00:02:55.420
And we're excited by the fact
that retailers are continuing

00:02:55.420 --> 00:02:58.250
to add contactless readers
to their point of sale.

00:02:58.250 --> 00:03:01.010
And there'll be a lot more
places to use it.

00:03:01.010 --> 00:03:05.060
In terms of the reference that
you made to our support for

00:03:05.060 --> 00:03:07.660
all cards in the Wallet, we're
really excited by the

00:03:07.660 --> 00:03:10.870
announcement we made at the
beginning of August where

00:03:10.870 --> 00:03:13.840
Google Wallet now supports all
your credit and debit cards.

00:03:13.840 --> 00:03:17.540
So you can link any Visa,
MasterCard, Amex, Discover

00:03:17.540 --> 00:03:21.670
branded card to your Wallet
and use it not only for

00:03:21.670 --> 00:03:24.820
in-store purchases using the
phone but use it online as

00:03:24.820 --> 00:03:27.680
well at participating
retailers.

00:03:27.680 --> 00:03:32.040
And the nice thing about Google
Wallet is the Wallet

00:03:32.040 --> 00:03:34.960
could also be used for purchases
through Google

00:03:34.960 --> 00:03:38.460
Properties as well, like the
Google store where you could

00:03:38.460 --> 00:03:41.130
buy applications,
digital content.

00:03:41.130 --> 00:03:44.260
You can also use it to buy
digital content through

00:03:44.260 --> 00:03:47.050
YouTube as well as the Chrome
store and other

00:03:47.050 --> 00:03:47.960
properties as well.

00:03:47.960 --> 00:03:51.470
So Google Wallet is really
becoming the central way to

00:03:51.470 --> 00:03:57.250
make purchases, not only on
Google Properties but in store

00:03:57.250 --> 00:03:58.880
as well as online as well.

00:03:58.880 --> 00:04:00.180
MIHAI IONESCU: Sounds
exciting.

00:04:00.180 --> 00:04:01.360
How about a demo?

00:04:01.360 --> 00:04:03.470
Can you show us how the
new Wallet works?

