on two carrier networks,

00:17:34.170 --> 00:17:36.460
Virgin as well as Sprint.

00:17:36.460 --> 00:17:41.880
And we're looking to expand
our carrier distribution.

00:17:41.880 --> 00:17:44.600
We're in discussions today
with a number of other

00:17:44.600 --> 00:17:47.610
carriers and hope to make some
announcements over the next

00:17:47.610 --> 00:17:48.120
little while.

00:17:48.120 --> 00:17:50.230
So stay tuned for that.

00:17:50.230 --> 00:17:55.270
Just on the device question, we
are going to see NFC become

00:17:55.270 --> 00:17:57.800
a standard feature of every
smartphone device.

00:17:57.800 --> 00:18:01.730
This is a trend that is
taking place today.

00:18:01.730 --> 00:18:03.750
Actually, a very good indication
of that is the

00:18:03.750 --> 00:18:06.900
Galaxy S3, which launched
a little while ago.

00:18:06.900 --> 00:18:10.160
It sold 10 million devices
in the first two months.

00:18:10.160 --> 00:18:16.040
And this was a flagship device
of Samsung's and has NFC as a

00:18:16.040 --> 00:18:17.250
core feature in there.

00:18:17.250 --> 00:18:21.500
And what's driving the NFC
adoption in phones is not just

00:18:21.500 --> 00:18:25.410
the payments-use cases, but it's
also use cases like being

00:18:25.410 --> 00:18:31.610
able to share content between
devices as well as pairing,

00:18:31.610 --> 00:18:37.760
say, a handset as well as a set
of speakers or headphones

00:18:37.760 --> 00:18:38.860
to the device as well.

00:18:38.860 --> 00:18:41.210
So there's a lot more
applications for NFC.

00:18:41.210 --> 00:18:45.200
And you will see NFC become
a core feature just like

00:18:45.200 --> 00:18:48.430
cameras, Bluetooth, Wi-Fi,
things that we kind of take

00:18:48.430 --> 00:18:50.272
for granted today.

00:18:50.272 --> 00:18:55.030
Yeah, who thought a few years
ago that cameras would be in

00:18:55.030 --> 00:18:55.750
every smartphone?

00:18:55.750 --> 00:19:00.730
So NFC is going to take the
same position in terms of

00:19:00.730 --> 00:19:02.790
being a core feature
in devices.

00:19:02.790 --> 00:19:06.050
So that is actually
going to drive

00:19:06.050 --> 00:19:07.650
adoption of Google Wallet.

00:19:07.650 --> 00:19:11.810
And we're quite excited about
the trends that we're seeing

00:19:11.810 --> 00:19:12.530
in the market.

00:19:12.530 --> 00:19:12.860
MIHAI IONESCU: Great.

