00:20:16.140 --> 00:20:18.630
Let's talk a little bit about
other merchant-led

00:20:18.630 --> 00:20:21.280
initiatives, like the
MCX initiative.

00:20:21.280 --> 00:20:23.770
If you want to talk a little
bit about it or other

00:20:23.770 --> 00:20:26.140
wallet-related products.

00:20:26.140 --> 00:20:27.270
ROBIN DUA: Sure.

00:20:27.270 --> 00:20:29.685
So this is actually a really
good point that there's going

00:20:29.685 --> 00:20:31.170
to be a lot of wallets
out there over

00:20:31.170 --> 00:20:32.590
the next little while.

00:20:32.590 --> 00:20:36.320
And we actually think it's a
great thing for there to be

00:20:36.320 --> 00:20:39.810
lots of competition because it
actually makes the product

00:20:39.810 --> 00:20:40.850
better at the end of the day.

00:20:40.850 --> 00:20:43.230
It forces everybody to really
think through what are the

00:20:43.230 --> 00:20:44.910
user experiences that
people want.

00:20:44.910 --> 00:20:48.795
And it forces everybody to build
better products at the

00:20:48.795 --> 00:20:50.030
end of the day.

00:20:50.030 --> 00:20:51.980
It also helps on two
other fronts.

00:20:51.980 --> 00:20:56.880
One is those wallets out there
that are taking an approach to

00:20:56.880 --> 00:21:01.140
use NFC technology in the phone
are actually going to

00:21:01.140 --> 00:21:04.710
encourage retailers to install
contactless readers into their

00:21:04.710 --> 00:21:06.470
point-of-sale system.

00:21:06.470 --> 00:21:10.195
So this will actually result
in much greater interest on

00:21:10.195 --> 00:21:12.210
the part of retailers
to upgrade

00:21:12.210 --> 00:21:14.960
point-of-sale terminals.

00:21:14.960 --> 00:21:17.930
And the other effect that it
has is on the device side.

00:21:17.930 --> 00:21:21.900
I think OEMs are already
motivated by the exciting use

00:21:21.900 --> 00:21:24.290
cases that NFC offers.

00:21:24.290 --> 00:21:30.420
But with more wallet providers
out there and consumers having

00:21:30.420 --> 00:21:34.660
a choice, I think OEMs will be
much more motivated to put NFC

00:21:34.660 --> 00:21:35.700
into their devices.

00:21:35.700 --> 00:21:40.230
So all of these things will
actually result in increased

00:21:40.230 --> 00:21:43.020
momentum around mobile payments
in the market, which

00:21:43.020 --> 00:21:45.830
I think is a great thing
for Google as well.

00:21:45.830 --> 00:21:48.660
The other thing I just want
to highlight is from the

00:21:48.660 --> 00:21:51.110
standpoint of differentiation.

00:21:51.110 --> 00:21:53.700
We've adopted a new approach
as part of our

00:21:53.700 --> 00:21:55.230
recent Wallet release.

00:21:55.230 --> 00:21:57.880
We've moved the Wallet
to the cloud.

00:21:57.880 --> 00:22:01.890
And all a user's payment
credentials are now stored

00:22:01.890 --> 00:22:04.620
securely on servers
in the cloud.

00:22:04.620 --> 00:22:08.050
And what this offers users the
ability to do is access their

00:22:08.050 --> 00:22:11.950
Wallet through any device
and through any channel.

00:22:11.950 --> 00:22:17.110
And under the old model that
we had, we were actually

00:22:17.110 --> 00:22:19.340
integrating with each
card issuer.

00:22:19.340 --> 00:22:23.470
And this integration, from the
time of negotiation to

00:22:23.470 --> 00:22:24.900
integration, would take
anywhere from

00:22:24.900 --> 00:22:26.510
six months to a year.

00:22:26.510 --> 00:22:30.110
And under this model, the
cards were stored in the

00:22:30.110 --> 00:22:33.220
secure element in
the NFC device.

00:22:33.220 --> 00:22:36.180
We just didn't feel that this
model was very scalable.

00:22:36.180 --> 00:22:38.820
It would literally take a
lifetime to get through the

00:22:38.820 --> 00:22:41.900
8,500 or so issuers that
are in the US.

00:22:41.900 --> 00:22:45.980
And so by adopting this
cloud-based approach, we

00:22:45.980 --> 00:22:50.020
greatly simplified not only the
user experience because

00:22:50.020 --> 00:22:53.220
now I could have a wallet with
all my cards and other

00:22:53.220 --> 00:22:58.270
credentials made available to
me through any channel.

00:22:58.270 --> 00:23:02.690
But it also gives me a lot of
flexibility to transact in

00:23:02.690 --> 00:23:05.400
ways that I didn't have the
opportunity to before.

00:23:05.400 --> 00:23:11.100
But also on the issuer side,
issuers are excited about the

00:23:11.100 --> 00:23:14.610
new cloud-based approach because
the time to market for

00:23:14.610 --> 00:23:19.110
them in terms of enabling their
cards to work with NFC

00:23:19.110 --> 00:23:21.670
has been reduced
to almost zero.

00:23:21.670 --> 00:23:26.290
And in some cases, issuers could
say, I don't want to do

00:23:26.290 --> 00:23:27.030
any integration.

00:23:27.030 --> 00:23:31.380
I'm happy just providing you
with card art and having my

00:23:31.380 --> 00:23:34.470
card represented in
the Wallet so that

00:23:34.470 --> 00:23:36.680
consumers see my brand.

00:23:36.680 --> 00:23:39.570
But we also have a set of tools
and APIs that issuers

00:23:39.570 --> 00:23:42.630
could integrate if they want
to enable features like

00:23:42.630 --> 00:23:46.360
enabling their users to save
cards to the Wallet directly

00:23:46.360 --> 00:23:49.240
from internet banking or
mobile banking sites.

00:23:49.240 --> 00:23:51.790
And that's a really lightweight
integration that

00:23:51.790 --> 00:23:53.540
doesn't take six months
to a year.

00:23:53.540 --> 00:23:56.140
It actually just takes a matter
of days or a few weeks

00:23:56.140 --> 00:23:57.580
at the most.

00:23:57.580 --> 00:24:00.910
So I think this is actually
a really important point.

00:24:00.910 --> 00:24:04.530
Because there are a lot of
wallet providers out there

00:24:04.530 --> 00:24:08.720
that are stuck on this approach
of let's integrate

00:24:08.720 --> 00:24:16.670
with every issuer and let's
enable this over the year,

00:24:16.670 --> 00:24:19.060
provisioning of cards to
the secure element.

00:24:19.060 --> 00:24:21.630
And it's just not a
scalable approach.

00:24:21.630 --> 00:24:24.630
And it's not going to give
consumers access to every one

00:24:24.630 --> 00:24:26.580
of their cards that they have
in their leather wallet in

00:24:26.580 --> 00:24:27.740
their phone.

00:24:27.740 --> 00:24:30.020
PENG YING: So we're trying
to simplify it as much as

00:24:30.020 --> 00:24:31.140
possible for everybody.

00:24:31.140 --> 00:24:31.540
ROBIN DUA: Exactly.

00:24:31.540 --> 00:24:34.220
PENG YING: Ideally, it's one
click, add my card to Wallet,

00:24:34.220 --> 00:24:35.610
and then you're done.

00:24:35.610 --> 00:24:36.055
ROBIN DUA: That's it.

00:24:36.055 --> 00:24:36.910
That's it.

00:24:36.910 --> 00:24:40.820
And we wanted to make the Wallet
user experience, from

00:24:40.820 --> 00:24:44.900
the time of enrollment to
using it, super simple.

00:24:44.900 --> 00:24:46.160
And I think we've done that.

